Class TestRackSimulator1

java.lang.Object
  abstractModulePack.AbstractDeviceModule
      abstractModulePack.AbstractSignalModule
          simulatorPack.TestRackSimulator1
All Implemented Interfaces:
DeviceInterface, SignalInterface
public class TestRackSimulator1
extends AbstractSignalModule

TestRackSimulator1 simulates a test-rack that: 1. outputs data to four-ports simultaneously. 2. starts to output data at -10dbm. 3. after every measurement, the output power is decremented by 2dbm. 4. stops outputting power at -30dbm. We assume that the load resistance is 1ohm. There is a random noise that ranges from 0 - 0.001 volts. The simulator splits its signal to four pieces and sends over four ports.

Author:
tianzhao
